    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The State Capital And Places to Discover</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Katherine Kane letter lauds November 21 article on Hartford, Conn, which described it as city of surprises for tourists (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It was a pleasure to read your Nov. 21 article about Hartford (''For Tourists, the State Capital Is a City Full of Surprises.'')</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It was a pleasure to read your Nov. 21 article about Hartford (''For Tourists, the State Capital Is a City Full of Surprises.'')</p>
        <p>I moved to the city just a year ago to join the Harriet Beecher Stowe Center, and am excited to be a part of Hartford's revitalization. You found places in the city that I hadn't yet discovered!</p>
        <p>As I am sure you know, Harriet Beecher Stowe was an energetic writer, a woman who managed to balance a career and family in an era when that was extremely unusual, and whose book ''Uncle Tom 's Cabin'' was an immediate international best seller that galvanized the Abolitionist movement.</p>
        <p>Thank you for revealing some of the gems of our city.</p>
        <p>KATHERINE KANE  Executive Director  Harriet Beecher Stowe Center  Hartford</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
